OpenAPI 
    - It refers to the specification used to document the api using standardised formats, the formats used are json or yaml.
    - It contains set of rules or guidelines to define an api
    - It is language agnostic specification for describing APIs (ie) it can used to describe an api without using any specific language. The apis defined can be use to implement any of the programming language as per the preference of the developer or team

Benefits
1. Design API
     - It helps in designing an api, since it is language agnostic we can define api in generic terms and collect feedback from others before implementing. Any feedbacks can be easily incorporate in the design

2. Generate server side stubs
      - Once api design is fixed, we can use openapi document to generate server side stubs to implement api. It provides a quick template for the developer to start working on the project 

3. Generate client side SDK
      - Similarly it allows to generate client side SDK by the clients or any 3rd party systems. There are many languages they can use to generate SDK against openapi

4. Testing apis
      - Also it can be used as test client to test various operation defined in an api,since this api document captures list of operations, their parameters, expected request and response format etc, so it becomes lot easier for various tools to test the api accurately

5. API documentation
       - In case developer have already implemented an api, then using various openapi tools we can generate api document from the source codes

6. Understand API better
       - It allows non-technical members to understand the api better without need for programming experience

Swagger vs OpenAPI 
    In short the term Swagger refers to the tools provided by the smart Beer Company, whereas open API refers to the API specification defined and maintained by the open API initiative. The confusion arises when smart beer renamed Swagger API specification to open API specification,
until version 2.0.0 it was referred to as Swagger specification, however from 3.0.0 it is referred to as open API specification. 
   In open API specification you can either use yaml or Json to define an open API document, it
has got metadata about API such as version, information about API, external document references, tags to group operations, parts that define operations on various resources and so on. The tool
that was used to create this open API specification is Swagger editor. We have another tool
from Swagger namely Swagger UI which shows the open API specification in a nice UI format which is easy to understand, it shows the operations defined against various resources also so you can try out the operations defined using the same UI 

