Designing REST API using OpenAPI for student system
     We have student resource with the operations, to get a specific student based on a query parameter and in the query parameter student name will be passed, we will have a post operation to add a new student and then we will also see that how we can have pass a path parameter with a student ID to get single student

1. First we want to add the basic information (ie) metadata of our API which includes info tag

openapi: 3.0.3
info:
  title: Student API
  description: Student Demo API
  contact:   #add contact details
     name: ABC
     url: http://abc.com
  version: 1.0.0

#Add multiple servers
servers:
  - url: http://devapi.com
  - url: http://prodapi.com

2. Add the paths where we specify your API resources and then within those resources you will specify your operations like get, post etc
   First we write path /student for the student resource and inside this we write the description, next we define the operations which are basically the HTTP get operation where user can query
information about some students based on provided query parameter.

paths:
   /student:
       description: Student Resource
       get:

   To specify parameters we use "parameters" option and inside this we choose whether it's going to be a header parameter or query parameter or what type of parameter, so we will choose "query"
parameter and then we will write the name of this parameter as studentname and then we specify  "required" as true because we want to keep studentname query parameter as mandatory, and then we want to specify the schema where we are going to specify type of studentname as string and we write the "example" as Ram 

paths:
   /student:
       description: Student Resource
       get:
         description: Operation to Fetch Student
         parameters:
            - in: query
              name: studentname
              required: true
              schema:
                 type: string
                 example: Ram

   Next we want to specify the response using "responses" and inside the responses we are going to
specify which HTTP code we are going to write this response, in the production and the real scenarios you need to make sure we coverall of the response codes and also a default scenario, but in our case we will just go for 200 code which is a response success.
   We select "content" whether we want json or XML and  define all the details of your response and request payloads within the details of your operation 
   In the schemas we specify type and in case of this get operation we are expecting an array of students for the same name so we will choose it as an array where we define all the
details of the student. 

paths:
   /student:
       description: Student Resource
       get:
         description: Operation to Fetch Student
         parameters:
            - in: query
              name: studentname
              required: true
              schema:
                 type: string
                 example: Ram
         responses:
            200:
              description: Success Response
              content:
                 application/json
                    schema:
                       type: array
                       items:
                          properties:
                             StudentID:
                                type: integer
                                example: 3
                             StudentName:
                                type: string
                                example: Sam
                             StudentRemarks:
                                type: string
                                example: High Grade Student

we have defined the response structure as the student array which contain student object and each student object will have student ID, student name and student remarks  

3. Now we define post operation using "post" method and now within the post we write the
"description" 
   In case of post we have to specify requestbody in a json format with the student object and using "content" and choose what kind of content it's expecting so we write application/json 
   We have to write the "schema" for student object using "object"  since we are expecting only one object and we provide all the properties 
   Next we will add the responses with HTTP code 201 with description 

post:
  description: Add a new Student
  requestBody:
     content:
        application/json:
           schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                 StudentID:
                    type: integer
                    example: 3
                 StudentName:
                    type: string
                    example: Sam
                 StudentRemarks:
                    type: string
                    example: High Grade Student
  responses:
     201:
       description: Record successfully added          


4. Next we want to have our student resource with path parameter, so we first write "/student/{id}", first we give "description" after that we want to use "get" operation and in the same way we will add the "parameters" by choosing as "path" because this is going to be a path
parameter and then the name of this parameter as id, we have to specify as "required" to true,
and then we have to specify "schema" where we specifiy type  as integer
   Next we specify "responses" for 200 with description, then we are going to select content as application/json and then inside that we are going specify the schema with all its properties 

/student/{id}:
   description: Get Student based on Path parameter
   get:
      parameters:
         - in: path
           name: id
           required: true
           schema:
              type: integer 
      responses:
         200:
           description: Success Response with Path Param
           content:
              application/json
                 schema:
                    type: array
                    items:
                          properties:
                             StudentID:
                                type: integer
                                example: 3
                             StudentName:
                                type: string
                                example: Sam
                             StudentRemarks:
                                type: string
                                example: High Grade Student


Now we have all the operations ready, if you see here we have a get operation which is
expecting student name, we have post operation which is expecting Json as a request body and we have a student with path parameters which is the third operation available.

5. Instead of writing request and response schemas each and every time, we want to write the schemas at our root level and reuse in other operations, for that we have to use "components"

components:
   schemas:
      student:
         type: object
         properties:
            StudentID:
               type: integer
               example: 3
            StudentName:
               type: string
               example: Sam
            StudentRemarks:
               type: string
               example: High Grade Student
      students:
         type: array
         items:
            properties:
               StudentID:
                  type: integer
                  example: 3
               StudentName:
                  type: string
                  example: Sam
               StudentRemarks:
                  type: string
                  example: High Grade Student
 
We have created a schema object with the name student and another schema object called students 
inside components, now we need to refer to these components instead of writing all these schemas within each and every operation using "$ref"

/student:
       description: Student Resource
       get:
         description: Operation to Fetch Student
         parameters:
            - in: query
              name: studentname
              required: true
              schema:
                 type: string
                 example: Ram
         responses:
            200:
              description: Success Response
              content:
                 application/json
                    schema:
                       $ref: '#/components/schemas/students'

post:
  description: Add a new Student
  requestBody:
     content:
        application/json:
           schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/student'
  responses:
     201:
       description: Record successfully added 


/student/{id}:
   description: Get Student based on Path parameter
   get:
      parameters:
         - in: path
           name: id
           required: true
           schema:
              type: integer 
      responses:
         200:
           description: Success Response with Path Param
           content:
              application/json
                 schema:
                    $ref: '#/components/schemas/students'


Now we have all of our operations are referring to respective components which have been defined for our API 


